SUMMARY:Safe Harbor Park Field Trip
DESCRIPTION:Kim Morelock will lead a field trip to Safe Harbor Park in search of the Yellow-throated Warbler and other early spring migrants. Meet at the Safe Harbor Park tennis court by 7 a.m. Much of the time will be spent walking through the park along the Conestoga River and Warehouse Road. The trip will end by scoping the Susquehanna River below the dam from the platform viewing area. Contact Kim at 717-471-0787\, or email motherunitof5@aol.com by 6 p.m. the night before if you plan to attend. \n  \nMeeting Location: Safe Harbor Park Tennis Courts near 5365 River Rd.\, Conestoga\, PA 17516\nContact: Kim Morelock\, 717-471-0787 or motherunitof5@aol.com  
URL:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/event/safe-harbor-park-field-trip/
LOCATION:Safe Harbor Park Tennis Courts (Meetup Location)\, 5365 River Rd.\, Conestoga\, PA\, 17516\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/IMG_0253.jpeg
END:VEVENT
