SUMMARY:Monthly Club Meeting - Bird Safe Harrisburg\, 2025: A Year in Review
DESCRIPTION:Club Meeting – Middle Creek Wildlife Management Area Visitor Center\, 100 Museum Road\, Stevens\, PA 17578 \nPresented by Zach Richard\, Bird Safe Harrisburg Chair \nCollisions with windows kill over one billion birds in the United States each year. This problem is frequently documented by collision monitoring programs all over the world. Bird Safe Harrisburg’s program aims to identify the timing of collisions\, the species most affected\, and the most deadly buildings in Harrisburg. See how the work done in 2025 will help support future conservation goals and learn how you can be involved in being part of the solution.\n\nSpeaker Bio: Zach Richard is a Licensed Professional Geologist with the Department of Environmental Protection. He is a former President of Appalachian Audubon Society and now serves on the Board of the Pennsylvania Audubon Council. He is the founder and Chair of Bird Safe Harrisburg\, a committee of Appalachian Audubon Society that strives to make our built environment less lethal to birds.
URL:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/event/monthly-club-meeting-bird-safe-harrisburg-2025-a-year-in-review/
LOCATION:Middle Creek Wildlife Management Area Visitor Center\, 100 Museum Road\, Stevens\, PA\, 17578\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/IMG_6420.jpeg
END:VEVENT
