SUMMARY:Shenk's Ferry Wildflower Preserve Field Trip
DESCRIPTION:Cammy Freed will lead a field trip to Shenk’s Ferry Wildflower Preserve to observe birds and the wide selection of wildflowers\, including Trillium\, Virginia Bluebells\, and Dutchman’s Britches. Participants will meet at the Safe Harbor Park Tennis Courts at 7 a.m. After a short period of birding at Safe Harbor Park we will head to Shenk’s Ferry. Trip limited to 15 participants. Wear sturdy walking shoes and bring binoculars. This trail will be mostly level and well-groomed. The walk is anticipated to last 3 to 4 hours. Contact Cammy at 717-368-1979 or cameala@gmail.comif you have any questions and by 6 p.m. the day before if you plan to participate. \nMeeting Location: Safe Harbor Park Tennis Courts near 5365 River Rd.\, Conestoga\, PA 17516\nContact: Cammy Freed\, 717-368-1979 or cameala@gmail.com
URL:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/event/shenks-ferry-wildflower-preserve-field-trip/
LOCATION:Safe Harbor Park Tennis Courts (Meetup Location)\, 5365 River Rd.\, Conestoga\, PA\, 17516\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/IMG_0257.jpeg
END:VEVENT
