SUMMARY:Safe Harbor Park Field Trip
DESCRIPTION:Carl Groff will lead a field trip at Safe Harbor Park. Meet at 8 a.m. at the Safe Harbor Park tennis courts. The focus will be on different habitats within the park. Some target birds include Yellow-throated Warbler\, Palm Warbler\, Blue-gray Gnatcatcher and Warbling Vireo. Walking will be mostly level and dry. Bring water and snacks. There is a porta-john at the park. Please contact Carl at 717-471-9969 or fledge19@verizon.net by 6 p.m. the previous day if you plan to attend. \n  \nMeeting Location: Safe Harbor Park Tennis Courts near 5365 River Rd.\, Conestoga\, PA 17516\nContact: Carl Groff\, 717-471-9969 or fledge19@verizon.net 
