SUMMARY:Chickies Rock Warbler Walk
DESCRIPTION:Marie Johnston will lead a field trip to Chickies Rock County Park. Meet at 7 a.m. at Breezy View Overlook along Rt. 441 just north of Columbia. After birding Breezy View\, which includes a view of a Bald Eagle’s nest on the York County side of the Susquehanna River\, the group will proceed to the Chickies Rock Overlook parking lot and bird in the park on both sides of Rt. 441. The field trip will end in the day-use area of the park. In addition to warblers\, target species include orioles\, tanagers\, and flycatchers. Be prepared for ticks and bring water and snacks/lunch. Contact Marie (717-413-2086 or mariejohnston303@gmail.com) if you have questions or by 6 p.m. on the previous day if you plan to attend. \nMeeting Location: Breezy View Overlook near 770 Breezyview Dr.\, Columbia\, PA 17512\nContact: Marie Johnston\, 717-413-2086\, mariejohnston303@gmail.com
URL:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/event/chickies-rock-warbler-walk/
LOCATION:Chickies Rock Breezy View Overlook (Meeting Location)\, 770 Breezyview Dr.\, Columbia\, PA\, 17512\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://lancasterbirdclub.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/47954985173_423dd0452c_o.jpeg
