SUMMARY:Northwest River Trail Field Trip
DESCRIPTION:Warren and Nina Wolf will lead a field trip on the Northwest River Trail. Participants should plan to meet at the Conoy Wetlands Preserve / Prescot Road Parking Lot. In addition to birds\, there is also the possibility of wildflowers in bloom. Wear sturdy walking shoes and bring binoculars. The walk is anticipated to last between 3 and 4 hours and will be on a level well-groomed trail. Contact Warren and Nina at 717-284-2663 or wolfers@aol.com if you have any questions and by 6 p.m. the day before if you plan to participate.  \n  \nMeeting Location: Conoy Wetlands Preserve\, Prescot Rd off River Rd\, Bainbridge\, PA 17502 (Exact GPS location of parking: 40.1072561\,-76.6865055)\nContact: Warren and Nina Wolf\, 717-284-2663 or wolfers@aol.com 
